               <div type="commentary">
                  <p>Due to damage to the support, the year numeral is lost. Through trial and error, we find that the only year of Balitung’s reign (820–832 Śaka), for which the surviving calendar elements coincide is 824 Śaka (see the calculation derived from the HIC software below). As such, we propose that the lost year is 824 Śaka, thereby deriving the Julian date equivalent of 29 October 902 CE.</p>
                  <p>In this hand, the pasangan -va is sometimes difficult to distinguish from the suku, e.g. lamvit· (1v4), mu⟨A⟩ṁ (1v6).</p>
               </div>
